comments.body: `void` is not the same as `any`. Please use `any` if the return type is not confirmed from docs.
Using any in my opinion is incorrect when the docs do not mention any return types. For all the methods that I put void for the Raphael docs did not have any explicit return information.
e.g. this should be `RaphaelElement` . I would accept `any` but `void` is wrong.
Right. The docs return object so RaphaelElement or any is probably the way to go.
I noticed you removed `optional` i.e. `?` is this intentional?

Yes, the reference documentation has explicit parameters so that's why I removed the option annotation. Adding them back in is probably also ok. I'm not very familiar with the Raphael APIs so I leave this one to you.
